dquo; said</span><strong>Grace Lee</strong><span>, lead makeup artist for&nbsp;</span><strong>Maybelline New York</strong><span>. The chocolate shaded smoky eyes were the focus of the look: Lee lined models&rsquo; eyes on the top and bottom using Maybelline Eye Studio Master Smoky Longwearing Shadow-Pencil in &ldquo;Scorching Brown&rdquo; (</span><em>$9,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://well.ca/products/maybelline-eye-studio-master-smoky_79867.html\">well.ca</a></em><span>) and then smudged the colour to create a rough, undone look. For a glossy sheen on eyelids and the top of cheekbones, Lee lightly applied Maybelline Baby Lips (</span><em>$4,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://well.ca/products/maybelline-baby-lips_39317.html\">well.ca</a></em><span>). Meanwhile, models&rsquo; actual lips were covered with the shiny but non-sticky Maybelline Color Elixer gloss in &ldquo;Caramel Infused&rdquo; (</span><em>$9, at drugstores November 2013</em><span>)&mdash;which Lee proclaimed &ldquo;the product of the season.&rdquo;</span></p>',NULL),(45,37,'vi','A tale of two spirits','a-tale-of-two-spirits','Silk muslin scarf','<p>French designer <strong>Linda Mai Phung</strong> and the designers at <strong>Gris Neutre</strong> have finally made it possible to wrap yourself in an ancient Vietnamese fairytale. Thoughtfully put to muslin, this beautifully intricate pattern illustrates the ancient tale of Sea Spirit Thuy Tinh, and Mountain Spirit Son Tinh, both vying for the hand of the daughter of King Hung Vuong XVIII. Their epic battle is said to have been the origin of the monsoon season in Vietnam and one that has continued to be fought every year since.</p>\r\n<p>The <strong>Gris Neutre for Linda Mai Phuong</strong> collection includes a range of accessories and a line of clothing in silk, organic cotton and linen, each piece expressing the struggle of Thuy Tinh and Son Tinh&rsquo;s natural rivalry.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL),(47,37,'en','A tale of two spirits','a-tale-of-two-spirits-